    Use %Nm filename pattern for PGO

    %p expands to the process ID. While unlikely, PID collisions can occur,
    leading to loss of data.

    The %Nm syntax creates a pool of files of size N and the PGO instrumentation
    code picks a file (based on PID % N). If there is a conflict, merging mode
    is used, which utilizes file locking to update the file in place so data
    loss cannot occur.

    See the source code at 
    https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/blob/main/compiler-rt/lib/profile/InstrProfilingFile.c.

diff --git a/configure.ac b/configure.ac
index 82cf6f938a..13db5547e1 100644
--- a/configure.ac
+++ b/configure.ac
@@ -2062,8 +2062,8 @@
             -output=\"\$(shell pwd)/code.profclangd\"
             \"\$(shell pwd)\"/*.profclangr
     ")
-    LLVM_PROF_FILE="LLVM_PROFILE_FILE=\"\$(shell pwd)/code-%p.profclangr\""
-    LLVM_MERGED_DATA_FILE="\$(shell pwd)/code.profclangd"
+     LLVM_PROF_FILE="LLVM_PROFILE_FILE=\"\$(shell pwd)/code-%128m.profclangr\""
+     LLVM_MERGED_DATA_FILE="\$(shell pwd)/code.profclangd"
     if test $LLVM_PROF_FOUND = not-found
     then
       LLVM_PROF_ERR=yes
